  "decision_conditions": [
    "Condition : 1 - The work to which this consent relates shall be begun not later than three years from the date of this consent. \r\nReason: To comply with the requirements of Section 18 of the Planning (Listed Buildings and Conservation Areas) Act 1990, Section 51 of the Planning and Compulsory Purchase Act 2004 and the Town and Country Planning (Development Management Procedure) (England) Order 2015.\r\n",
    "Condition : 2 - The works of demolition/alteration hereby authorised shall be carried out in complete accordance with the following plans and specifications:\r\n[3804-FBR-A1-00-DR-A-200 rev. P01; 3804-FBR-A1-XX-DR-A-300 rev. P01; 3804-FBR-A1-XX-DR-A-301 rev. 301; roof condition report dated September 2022 ref. 22.3804; supplementary roof replacement report dated 15.02.2023 ref. no. 2023/0385; parapet assessment report dated 11 January 2023 ref. 62035/JW.]\r\nReason: To safeguard the character of the building, in accordance with Council policy LP3 of the Local Plan (adopted July 2023).\r\n",
    "Condition : 3 - Following removal of existing roof coverings a detailed schedule of identified necessary repairs required to any existing roof structures, including a method statement for those repair/replacement works, shall  be submitted to and approved in writing by the local planning authority prior to commencement of the works to the roof structure. The works shall be carried out in accordance with the approved schedule. \r\nReason: To safeguard the character of the listed building, in accordance with Council policy LP3 of the Local Plan (adopted July 2023) coupled with the requirements of the National Planning Policy Framework 2021.\r\n",
    "Condition : 4 - Prior to their use in the development details and samples of any new slates, including colour and type, shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the local planning authority. The development shall be carried out in accordance with the approved materials.\r\nReason: To safeguard the character of the listed building, in accordance with Council policy LP3 of the Local Plan (adopted July 2023) coupled with the requirements of the National Planning Policy Framework 2021..\r\nFramework 2021.",
    "Condition : 5 - Prior to its use a specification for a new liquid applied high performance waterproofing system for the flat roofs shall be submitted to and approved in wriitng by the local planning authority. The works shall be carried out in accordance with the approved specification. \r\nReason: To safeguard the character of the listed building, in accordance with Council policy LP3 of the Local Plan (adopted July 2023) coupled with the requirements of the National Planning Policy Framework 2021.\r\n",
    "Condition : 6 - Any rainwater goods that require replacement should be replaced with cast iron rainwater goods, unless otherwise agreed in writing by the local planning authority. \r\nReason: In the interest of the appearance of the listed building, in accordance with Council policy LP3 of the local plan (adopted July 2023) coupled with the requirements of the National Planning Policy Framework 2021.\r\n"
  ],
